SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: hpesbgn03763en_us
Version: 1

HPESBGN03763 rev.1 - HPE SiteScope, Disclosure of Sensitive Information, Bypass Security Restriction, Remote Arbitrary Code Execution

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2017-06-26
Last Updated: 2017-06-26

Potential Security Impact: Local: Bypass Security Restrictions, Disclosure of Sensitive Information; Remote: Arbitrary Code Execution

Source: Hewlett Packard Enterprise, Product Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified in HPE SiteScope. The vulnerabilities could be exploited to allow disclosure of sensitive information, bypass security restriction, and remote arbitrary code execution.

References:

  - CVE-2017-8952 - Authentication issue, Remote Arbitrary Code Execution
  - CVE-2017-8949 - Cryptographic Issue, Local Disclosure of Sensitive Information
  - CVE-2017-8950 - Cryptographic Issue, Local Disclosure of Sensitive Information
  - CVE-2017-8951 - Local Bypass Security Restrictions

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.

  - HP SiteScope Monitors Software Series - v11.2x, v11.3x

BACKGROUND

  CVSS Base Metrics
  =================
  Reference, CVSS V3 Score/Vector, CVSS V2 Score/Vector

    CVE-2017-8949
      6.7 CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:N
      5.0 (AV:L/AC:M/Au:S/C:C/I:P/A:N)

    CVE-2017-8950
      6.7 CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:N
      5.0 (AV:L/AC:M/Au:S/C:C/I:P/A:N)

    CVE-2017-8951
      7.4 CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H
      5.0 (AV:L/AC:M/Au:S/C:C/I:P/A:N)

    CVE-2017-8952
      8.1 CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H
      9.3 (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)

    Information on CVSS is documented in
